# Gogo Project Structure Rules

Use this rule when creating apps, moving code, wiring project-level packages, or
deciding where a feature belongs.

## Layout

- `{{.ProjectName}}/` contains project-level wiring: settings, root URLs, admin
  site construction, middleware, queue setup, and application bootstrap.
- `apps/` contains first-party app packages. Each app should be cohesive and own
  its domain behavior.
- `templates/`, `static/`, `media/`, `fixtures/`, and `tests/` are project-level
  support directories.
- `deploy/` contains deploy templates and infrastructure entrypoints.

## App Ownership

Create a new app when a domain has its own models, routes, APIs, admin entries,
forms, tasks, permissions, or templates.

Inside an app:

- Put model metadata and model helpers in `models.go`.
- Put migrations under `migrations/`.
- Put admin registrations in `admin.go`.
- Put HTTP route handlers in `urls.go`.
- Put API routes and viewsets in `api.go`.
- Put serializers in `serializers.go`.
- Put forms in `forms.go`.
- Put tasks in `tasks.go`.
- Put permission constants/helpers in `permissions.go`.
- Put reusable business logic in `services.go`.
- Put app tests under `tests/`.

## Imports

- Import only public Gogo packages, such as `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo/app`,
  `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo/models`, `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo/http`,
  `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo/admin`, `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo/api`,
  `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo/forms`, and `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo/queue`.
- Do not import `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo/internal`.
- Keep project-specific packages under this module path, not inside the Gogo
  framework module.

## Generated Files

Generated files are starting points owned by this project after creation. Keep
local changes focused and do not regenerate over hand-edited files unless that
is the explicit task.
